    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-04-29T18:50:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-04-29T18:50:00-05:00" n="252"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d252">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.11/4–2953: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy at Saigon</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d252fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_BPW1">Philip W.
                            Bonsal</persName>, Director of <gloss target="#t_PSA1">PSA</gloss>.
                        Repeated for information to Paris as telegram 5447.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-04-29T19:50:00-04:00"
                            >April 29, 1953—7:50 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2088. Embassy Despatch 429<note n="2" xml:id="d252fn2">Despatch 429 from Saigon,
                        Apr. 9, titled “French Diplomatic Assessment of <persName corresp="#p_BD1"
                            >Bao Dai</persName>,” is not printed. (751G.00/4–953)</note> states
                        <persName corresp="#p_BD1">Bao Dai</persName> requested exchange control
                    authorities transfer eighty million francs his credit France <pb facs="0560"
                        n="528" xml:id="pg_528"/> connection his forthcoming trip and describes
                    previous exchange transfers and benefits realized by <persName corresp="#p_BD1"
                        >Bao Dai</persName>. Department refers this connection views expressed
                        <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 294, Aug 8, 1952. Has not time
                    come for French take firm stand against <persName corresp="#p_BD1">Bao
                        Dai</persName>’s financial extravagances which contrast so deplorably with
                    efforts being made by France and US.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
